name: beta-fructofuranosidase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
reaction: Hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing beta-D-fructofuranoside residues in beta-D-fructofuranosides
comment: Substrates include sucrose; also catalyses fructotransferase reactions.

references.title: Invertases.
references.journal: In: Boyer, P.D., Lardy, H. and Myrback, K. (Eds.), The Enzymes, 2nd ed., vol. 4, Academic Press, New York, 1960, p. 379-396.

references.title: Purification and properties of yeast invertase.
